Summary of ReactJS Features:
Component-Based Architecture: Reusable components for better maintainability.
Virtual DOM: Efficient rendering and updates.
One-Way Data Binding: Predictable state management.
Declarative UI: Easier to reason about the UI state.
JSX: HTML-like syntax inside JavaScript.
React Hooks: State and lifecycle methods in functional components.
Lifecycle Methods: Control component behavior at different stages.
Context API: Global state management without prop drilling.
SSR and SEO Optimization: Faster page loads and better SEO.
Code-Splitting: Lazy loading for performance optimization.
React Developer Tools: Easy debugging and inspection.